{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox settlement | name = Anetan | settlement_type = [[Districts of Nauru|District]] | image_skyline = | imagesize = 250px | image_caption = | image_flag = | image_shield = | nickname = | motto = | image_map = Anetan in Nauru.svg | mapsize = | map_caption = Anetan District within Nauru | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{NRU}} | subdivision_type1 = [[Constituencies of Nauru|Constituency]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Anetan Constituency|Anetan]] | established_title = | established_date = | established_title1 = <!--City rights--> | established_date1 = | leader_title = | leader_name = | area_magnitude = | area_total_km2 = 1 | area_land_km2 = | area_water_km2 = | population_as_of = 2011 | population_note = | population_total = 587 | population_footnotes = | population_metro = | population_density_km2 = | pushpin_map = | pushpin_map1 = | pushpin_label_position = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_map_caption1 = | pushpin_mapsize = | coordinates = {{coord|0|30|19|S|166|56|33|E|display=inline,title}} | timezone = ([[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]]) | utc_offset = | elevation_m = 25 | postal_code_type = [[Postal code]]| | postal_code = | area_code = [[Telephone numbers in Nauru|+674]] | blank_info = | blank1_info = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Anetan''' is a [[district]] in the [[Pacific Ocean|Pacific]] island nation of [[Nauru]]. It lies in [[Anetan Constituency]].
==Geography== It is located in the north of the island and covers an area of {{convert|1.0|km²|0|abbr=on}}. It is one of the smallest districts. The population is about 880.
==Main sights== This district contains [[State House (Nauru)|State House]] - the official residence of the President, and the weather station of the island.
==Education== {{seealso|Education in Nauru}} Anetan Infant School is in Anetan.<ref name=EdStats2015>"[https://prism.spc.int/component/advlisting/?view=download&format=raw&fileId=85 Education Statistics Digest 2015]." [[Department of Education (Nauru)]]. Retrieved on July 8, 2018. p. 47 (PDF p. 47).</ref> The primary and secondary schools serving all of Nauru are Yaren Primary School in [[Yaren District]] (years 1-3), Nauru Primary School in [[Meneng District]] (years 4-6), Nauru College in [[Denigomodu District]] (years 7-9), and [[Nauru Secondary School]] (years 10-12) in Yaren District.<ref name=OHCHR>[http://docstore.ohchr.org/SelfServices/FilesHandler.ashx?enc=6QkG1d/PPRiCAqhKb7yhsqMFgv33OTgoZv7ZAgL6thBs%2BJaDouDrmbrhkSKQnAJmPZ9UvJeFASCaHOYMWlSYYCuENbqZ7%2B4S5kzfEKujpCmbACo3%2BCb5LwxaXyHF2qjW Document by the]." [[OHCHR]]. Retrieved on 8 July 2018. "The Education system is {{sic|comprised |hide=y|of}} 10 schools, there are District Infant schools each[...]and finally Nauru Secondary School (Years 10-12) where compulsory education end at Year 12.[...]"</ref>
==Notable people== *The former [[President of Nauru]] [[Marcus Stephen]], who took office in 2007, is a member of the [[Parliament of Nauru]] representing the Anetan and [[Ewa District, Nauru|Ewa]] constituency.
