{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Black Banksia Falls | photo = | photo_width = | photo_caption = | map = New South Wales | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|33|56|55|S|150|01|04|E|type:waterbody_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref name=GNR>{{NSW GNR|id=SXlpWysE|title=Black Banksia Falls|accessdate=11 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Gazetteer of Australia|id=NSW6603|name=Black Banksia Falls}}</ref> | location = [[Central Tablelands]], [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]] | type = | elevation = | height = | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Black Banksia Falls''' is a [[waterfall]] that is located within the [[Kanangra-Boyd National Park]] in the [[Central Tablelands]] region of [[New South Wales]], [[Australia]].
