'''Robert David Hodgson''' (June 7, 1923 - December 4, 1979) was an [[United States of America|American]] geographer and an internationally recognized expert on geographic aspects of the law of the sea and maritime boundaries. Dr. Hodgson believed that broader understanding of geographic principles would reduce international conflicts.<ref>{{cite web|title=AAG Dissertation Research Grants|url=http://www.aag.org/cs/grants/dissertation}}</ref> The [[Hodgson Seamount]] was named after him.
== Works == * ''The technical delimitation of a modern equidistant boundary'' (1975). Self-published.<ref>{{cite web|title=University of Virginia Library|url=http://virgobeta.lib.virginia.edu/catalog/u3254794}}{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> * {{cite report|title=Islands: normal and special circumstances |publisher=U.S. Dept. of State. Bureau of Intelligence and Research| id=Research study, RGES-3 |year=1973}}<ref>{{cite web|title=University of Virginia Library|url=http://virgobeta.lib.virginia.edu/catalog/u1394139}}{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> * {{cite journal|title=Towards an objective analysis of special circumstances: bays, rivers, coastal and oceanic archipelagos and atolls |year=1972 |publisher=Law of the Sea Institute}} * {{cite book|title=The Changing Map of Africa |first=Robert D. |last=Hodgson |first2=Elvyn A. |last2=Stoneman|publisher=[[John Wiley & Sons|D. Van Nostrand]] |series=Van Nostrand searchlight book |volume=16|year=1968 }}<ref>{{cite web|title=University of Virginia Library|url=http://virgobeta.lib.virginia.edu/catalog/u580523|work=University of Virginia Library}}{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> * ''The Champlain-Richelieu Lowland: A Study in Historical Geography'' (dissertation, 1951) <ref>{{cite web|title=University of Michigan Mirlyn Holdings|url=http://mirlyn.lib.umich.edu/Record/002142562}}</ref>
== Personal life == Hodgson was married to Margaret Hodgson. Father to David, Laura, Susan, Peter, Mark, Amy, and Luke.
